The algorithm has figured that with the 3 extra clusters in k=6 compared ot k=3, it just used those extra
clusters to cluster the class with the best Entropy, therefore the 3 new extra clusters have the same entropy as
the k=3. The two other clusters where the two classes overlap remain the same. They have the worst entropy
because of this overlap whilst the third class is isolated. The k=3 cluster is better than k=6 since the extra
clusters are unecessary since it is just clustering further an already great cluster.
